.:: Puzzle 7x2-Level-4-3::.
City: new-york, nizza
There 2 different types of food: eggplant, kale
2 different games are played: canasta, snooker
The people's birthday is in 2 different months: april, june
There are 2 different nationalities: indian, colombian
2 different brands of cigars are smoked: bluemaster, old-henry
The people prefer 2 different music-genres: reggae, hip-hop
1. the old-henry-smoker is on the right of the person eating kale##1
2. the indian is in an odd position##4
3. the person who's birthday is in april is on the left of the person traveling to new-york##1
4. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the person playing canasta##3
5. the person playing snooker is on the left of the fan of reggae##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |     2      |
| City      | nizza       | new-york     |
| Food         | kale | eggplant    |
| Game           | snooker   | canasta |
| Birthday   | april     | june     |
| Nationality           | indian     | colombian      |
| Cigar         | bluemaster     | old-henry     |
| Music-Genre     | hip-hop  | reggae        |

